        "Patients treated, especially with penicillin, may experience Jarisch-Herxheimer reactions, which may be severe.",
        "The American Academy of Pediatrics endoses that doxycycline can safely be administered for short durations (<=21 days) regardless of patient age (AAP Red Book 2018, Section 4; J Pediatr 166:1246, 2015)",
